sì /si4/
1. four; 4
2. to feed (a person or animal)
3. to seem; to appear; to resemble; similar; -like; pseudo-; (more) than
4. Buddhist temple; mosque; government office (old)
5. succession (to a title); to inherit; continuing (a tradition); posterity
6. to watch; to wait; to examine; to spy
7. 6th earthly branch: 9-11 a.m., 4th solar month (5th May-5th June), year of the Snake; ancient Chinese compass point: 150°
8. four (banker's anti-fraud numeral); unrestrained; wanton; (literary) shop
9. to raise; to rear; to feed
10. animal cited in ancient texts, resembling a buffalo (some say rhinoceros or female rhinoceros)
11. numeral 4 in the Suzhou numeral system »Sūzhōumǎzi«
12. (literary) to wait for
13. the end; to finish

15. spoon; ladle
16. stream which returns after branching
17. nasal mucus
18. river bank
19. to sacrifice; to offer libation to
20. square bamboo container for food or clothing
21. plow; plowshare
22. team of 4 horses

tà /ta4/
1. to tread; to stamp; to step on; to press a pedal; to investigate on the spot
2. to make a rubbing (e.g. of an inscription)
3. again and again; many
4. (bound form) to whip; to flog; (loanword) (pastry) tart (colloquial pr. »tǎ«)
5. couch
6. to step on
7. (literary) to drink; to swallow
8. to make a rubbing
9. a coarse, woollen serge
10. name of a river
11. to talk fast
12. abundant; mixed
13. to encase the end with metal
14. thallium
15. door or window in an upper story
16. door of an inner room
tà /ta4/
tàzhe, with the aspect particle -zhe marking a continuous state or ongoing action.

2. to make a rubbing (e.g. of an inscription)
3. again and again; many
4. (bound form) to whip; to flog; (loanword) (pastry) tart (colloquial pr. »tǎ«)
